9.3.1 Scimax enhancements to ob-ipython
---------------------------------------

We have made a few improvements to ob-ipython. Inline images are
supported now similar to how they are supported in the Jupyter
notebook. You specify the %matplotlib inline magic, and then plots will
appear "inline" along with any output from your cell block. The plots
are saved in a directory ipython-inline-images in filenames derived
from and md5 hash of the image. You can have more than one image, and
you also get the output from your block, similar to the way the Jupyter
notebook behaves.

